# Meteor build-system ignores. Works like .gitignore — matched paths
# are NOT scanned by the bundler / templating-compiler.
#
# Why these need to be here:
#   The brand/ and design/ folders hold standalone .html artefacts
#   (preview pages, logo concept galleries, branded email mock-ups)
#   that include their own <!DOCTYPE html> and <head>. Meteor's
#   templating-compiler treats every top-level .html file as a Blaze
#   template fragment and refuses to start when it sees <!DOCTYPE> or
#   bare <head>/<body>/<style> in a non-template file:
#     "Errors prevented startup… Can't set DOCTYPE here."
#
#   The right home for runtime markup is client/views/**. Everything
#   under brand/ and design/ is documentation / handoff material that
#   ships with the repo but never enters the bundle.
brand/
design/

# scripts/ are devOps utilities (PNG regen, etc.). Already excluded
# from prod by .dockerignore — also exclude from the Meteor bundle so
# any future .js helper in here doesn't accidentally end up server-side.
scripts/
